  "opposite_reasoning": "Following is the strongest opposite for Guiding because it represents the complementary role in a directional relationship. Where Guiding involves agency, control, and leading, Following involves receptivity, being controlled, and being led. This binary opposition is semantically clear, well-established in both WordNet and SUMO, and provides excellent utility for Fisher-LDA by capturing the fundamental distinction between active direction and passive reception of direction. For AI safety applications, distinguishing between guiding behaviors (autonomous, directive) and following behaviors (responsive, receptive) is valuable for monitoring agency and control patterns."
